There is a popular book titled, Black Tax. The thought-provoking collection of essays put together by award winning Niq Mhlongo depicts the reality of most black families and tries to answer this difficult question; is Black Tax a burden or Ubuntu? Over the weekend, I have been pondering on this question myself. I have a plethora of questions. Do you get married before you fix your parent’s house? Do you get married before you help your parents with varsity tuition fees for your siblings? Is there an expiry date to Black tax? Last week, a colleague of mine who is 26...